<h1>CHAPTER SYNOP SYSTEM — ARC 1 (85 Chapters)</h1>
<p style="font-size:11px;color:#555;">Enhanced with DLDS Master Guide + Character Charts. All factions represented. Lightbringer faction threads woven throughout. Official chapter titles integrated. Character-accurate voices, powers, and relationships used in all overviews.</p>

<h2>DIMENSIONLOCK: DEATHLY STORIES — Synop Lore Guide</h2>

<h3>CORE STORY THEMES</h3>
<ol style="font-size:12px; margin-bottom:10px;">
  <li>Learning to move on.</li>
  <li>Learning to forgive oneself.</li>
  <li>Finding what it means to be good in a world that's infinitely evil.</li>
  <li>Cherish the things that are close to us.</li>
</ol>

<h3>TASKS FOR WRITERS</h3>
<div class="tasks"><ul>
  <li>USE BOTH DIMENSIONLOCK:DS AND DS: OUTLINES TO FILL IN SYNOPSIS OVERVIEW BLANKS. REVIEW FOR NARRATIVE FLOW.</li>
  <li>ONLY USE FACTION FOCUS AND CHARACTER ARC FOCUS AFTER SCRIPTS ARE DONE.</li>
  <li>LORE PRIORITY = HOW MUCH THE CHAPTER CONTRIBUTES TO MAIN STORY. LOW = FILLER/FAN SERVICE.</li>
  <li>COMPLETED CHAPTERS INCLUDE 3 WEBCOMIC-FORMAT EPISODES.</li>
  <li>CHARACTER ARC AND OTHER ARC FOCUS TRACK CHARACTER PROGRESSION.</li>
  <li>WORLDBUILDING LORE REFERENCES FOUND IN THIS FOLDER AND EACH CHAPTER FOLDER.</li>
</ul></div>

<div class="lore-note" style="margin-top:10px;">⚠️ TENEBRIS RULE: The Tenebris CONTROLS the Sentry. The Sentry IS the Tenebris's will made physical — fiercely loyal, near-robotic, no self-preservation beyond mission completion. The Tenebris itself does not reveal until ~Ch. 77. It operates entirely in the shadows via the Sentry as its instrument.</div>
<div class="lore-note blue" style="margin-top:5px;">⚠️ LURKER RULE: The Lurker is a COMPLETELY SEPARATE threat. Not allied with or directed by the Tenebris. The Lurker and the Tenebris are actually IN COMPETITION — both want the Pure Madness. The Lurker is chaos. The Tenebris is strategy. They are rivals as much as they are threats to the protagonists.</div>
<div class="lore-note gold" style="margin-top:5px;">⚠️ LIGHTBRINGER FACTION: Metrodoria Lightbringer = God. Killed by the Tenebris in the prologue. Death loved her. Madoria AI = Daughter of God, fragmented, doesn't know her origin. She has the ability to purify the Madness — she doesn't know this yet. She recovers fragments of herself through the story. The Lightbringer faction threads through Sam's arc, Death's grief, and Madoria's awakening as the hidden counter-force to the Tenebris's darkness.</div>
<div class="lore-note purple" style="margin-top:5px;">⚠️ VIVIAN (GABRIEL FORGE): Shapeshifts by consuming bio-fragments of species. Has the Soul Splitter — a heavenly sword from a dead god (+97 Reality) made from NiteLite that lets him see seconds into the future. His Demon Destroyer form is from the Katára species, influenced by Tenebris — it attracts the Tenebris when used. He is impulsive, arrogant, lazy — but has a deep moral sense and forms bonds fast.</div>
<div class="lore-note orange" style="margin-top:5px;">⚠️ AGITATOR OF SIN: Immortal through reincarnation. Omega Blade bypasses physics. Can control others' bodies (not thoughts — victims are conscious and aware). Since he's an Admin, Death cannot see him. He believes both May AND Death are becoming heretics. He's idealistic but his arc ends in hypocrisy — he becomes exactly what he hates.</div>

