<div class="section-title">▶ ACT 1 — INTRODUCTION (Ch. 1–8)</div>

<table>
  <thead><tr>
    <th style="width:15%;">CHAPTER</th><th style="width:8%;">PRIORITY</th><th style="width:7%;">SOURCE</th>
    <th style="width:10%;">FACTION</th><th style="width:8%;">STATUS</th><th>OVERVIEW &amp; ARC NOTES</th>
  </tr></thead>
  <tbody>

  <tr><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 1</span><span class="official-title">"Sound of Devotion" P1/P2/P3</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-critical">Critical</span></td><td>CH1</td><td>Death Faction</td><td><span class="badge-finished">FINISHED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-may">MAY</span><span class="arc-tag tag-flybutt">FLYBUTT</span>
  May (age 9,999) and Flybutt introduced — the odd-couple dynamic of a half-reaper in training and her bloatfly familiar. Death's Ship, the Endless, and soul seed mechanics established. May uses her Magic Tarot Cards and Reaper Blade. Her Health Bracelet is shown in action. Flybutt acts as May's conscience and force field. First hint of May's scythe malfunction — Sidney stirring inside it. May fakes her emotions throughout — it reads as sharp and cold to everyone else.
  <div class="lore-note green">📌 FLYBUTT: Turned to stone once during this chapter when overstimulated — May barely notices. He reads soul seeds like a connoisseur, ID'ing each one by quality. A small detail that hints at his usefulness beyond comic relief.</div></td></tr>

  <tr><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 2</span><span class="official-title">"A Reaper's Banter"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-critical">Critical</span></td><td>CH2</td><td>Death Faction</td><td><span class="badge-finished">FINISHED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-death">DEATH</span><span class="arc-tag tag-may">MAY</span>
  Death's Ship interior established. Reapers going missing across Creation — Death is quietly alarmed but shows nothing. An evil entity within May is hinted at (the Madness connection). Trading hope introduced. The Agitator of Sin and Centurion Guard are established. Death tries to seem caring — it comes off robotic and strange, which is accurate to his character. Cryious is introduced as Death's shadow — loyal, dogmatic, quietly skeptical of May.
  <div class="lore-note gold">📌 DEATH: He likes crossword puzzles and notices the subtle beauty of life. He tries to express care for May but it reads wrong — flat delivery, no facial expression. This is not coldness. This is someone who doesn't know how to be warm. His arc begins here, invisibly.</div></td></tr>

  <tr><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 3</span><span class="official-title">"The Leap"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-critical">Critical</span></td><td>CH3</td><td>Death Faction</td><td><span class="badge-finished">FINISHED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-cryious">CRYIOUS</span><span class="arc-tag tag-may">MAY</span>
  Cryious properly introduced — robed, faceless, lightning bolt marking. He begins overseeing May's training. Uses his Mass Control power — weaponizing air into his scythe blades. He and Death move like mirrors of each other: both dogmatic, both blind to their own faults while seeing each other's clearly. May collects soul seeds. Reaper law established — no emotions, no deviation. Scythe malfunction continues.
  <div class="lore-note green">📌 CRYIOUS: He collects a small flower from a dying reality during this mission — lavender, his favorite. He says nothing about it. This is the first quiet hint of the Gardener of Creation thread.</div></td></tr>

  <tr><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 4</span><span class="official-title">"Lurking About"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-critical">Critical</span></td><td>CH4</td><td>Death Faction</td><td><span class="badge-finished">FINISHED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-may">MAY</span><span class="arc-tag tag-lurker">LURKER</span>
  May fights a frog demon that steals her hat. The hat/memory connection is introduced — without it, memories begin to blur. Sam watches from a distance — his first appearance, silent, studying. The Lurker is first mentioned indirectly: the frog demon carries a faint trace of corrupted madness that hints at something larger feeding the chaos in this reality.
  <div class="lore-note">📌 LURKER: He comes from outside Creation. He was once a scientist. Millions of years later nothing of that identity remains — only his obsession with corrupting Creation, because he believes Creation is impure. He envies May specifically because of the Madness inside her.</div></td></tr>

  <tr class="vivian-arc"><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 5</span><span class="official-title">"Paparazzi"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-critical">Critical</span></td><td>CH5</td><td>Death Faction</td><td><span class="badge-finished">FINISHED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-may">MAY</span><span class="arc-tag tag-vivian">VIVIAN</span><span class="arc-tag tag-lurker">LURKER</span>
  May and the Lurker meet directly. The Lurker recognizes May immediately — <em>"IT'S YOU! MAYTRIDALIS!!!"</em> — spinning and dancing with child-like excitement. He is obsessive, demented, relentless, lacks self-preservation. May fights back — aggressive, acrobatic, inelegant, exactly her style. She is gravely injured. The magical pouches heal her. Flybutt is left unconscious. May bumps into Vivian while retreating. The Lurker withdraws — not defeated, just entertained. He has been 5 steps ahead from the start.
  As the ship departs: Vivian (Gabriel Forge, last of his reality, using his mother's name in her honor) sneaks aboard using shapeshifting — consuming a bio-fragment to copy a crew member. He is inside Death's Ship. A one-million-year mission begins.
  <div class="lore-note purple">📌 VIVIAN'S SOUL SPLITTER: He carries it hidden under his projectile-proof trench coat. The heavenly sword made from NiteLite, taken from a dead god at +97 Reality, allows him to see seconds into the future. He has had it for centuries. It is the only weapon that has kept him alive long enough to reach this moment.</div></td></tr>

  <tr class="vivian-arc"><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 6</span><span class="official-title">"Cleansing"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-critical">Critical</span></td><td>CH6</td><td>Death Faction</td><td><span class="badge-finished">FINISHED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-vivian">VIVIAN</span><span class="arc-tag tag-may">MAY</span>
  May purifies a reality. Vivian, now inside the ship, tries shapeshifting into May — fails the voice. Flybutt exposes him. Vivian runs. Cornered, about to die, May enacts the Soul Contract — triggered by Vivian wearing her hat. He must prove his worth or die. The contract is a reaper law consequence: anyone who impersonates a reaper creates a Soul Contract as penance. May confronts her human soul about hope. She almost takes her hat off on purpose — doesn't.
  <div class="lore-note purple">📌 VIVIAN: He went to the Statue of the Leviathan. He walked through the portal, scared and surprised, but determined. He found May's room and determined she must be important. This was not random — he is strategic under the impulsiveness. He just didn't account for Flybutt.</div></td></tr>

  <tr class="vivian-arc"><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 7</span><span class="official-title">"Soul Contract"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-critical">Critical</span></td><td>CH7</td><td>Death Faction</td><td><span class="badge-finished">FINISHED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-vivian">VIVIAN</span><span class="arc-tag tag-may">MAY</span><span class="arc-tag tag-sam">SAM</span>
  May trains Vivian: soul catching, reaper law, what reapers can and can't do. Vivian reveals the Demon Destroyer form — based on the extinct Katára species influenced by the Tenebris. <strong>Using this form attracts the Tenebris.</strong> The Elite Reapers prepare for combat but don't engage. May goes quiet after talking with Sidney through her scythe — she questions whether she's been too mean. Death intrudes. May removes her hat on purpose to forget hope — the memory/hat connection deepens. Vivian calls Flybutt "Bloat."
  Sam appears briefly: born in Zero Point Reality, runs DimensionLight. He met Sydney at 13, lost her. He has crossed the endless searching for her. Midoriya AI pulls him away. May's scythe reacts to Sam's presence — she notices.
  May asks Vivian why he has a "girly name." He says it's for family remembrance. May pauses — <em>"I guess I understand family a little... We got a lot of work, weirdo."</em>
  <div class="lore-note teal">📌 SAM/LIGHTBRINGER: Sam was born in the Zero Point Reality — the First Reality. His parents died because of May's Madness. He doesn't know yet that May exists. His company DimensionLight is named after his hope of finding Sidney and is unknowingly named for the Lightbringer legacy his connection to Sidney carries.</div></td></tr>

  <tr class="iza-kiza"><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 8</span><span class="official-title">"Obedience Training"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-critical">Critical</span></td><td>CH8</td><td>Death Faction</td><td><span class="badge-finished">FINISHED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-iza">IZA</span><span class="arc-tag tag-kiza">KIZA</span><span class="arc-tag tag-agitator">AGITATOR</span>
  May, Vivian, Flybutt gather supplies. Death meets the Centurion chairman for the Obsidian Containment Unit's location. Kiza (spacey, no-filter, journalist who grew up in an orphanage with her brother, dreams of writing real adventure stories) and Izai (nervous new Guard member, outgoing, quick in battle, slow with feelings — always protecting Kiza since childhood) are introduced as adopted siblings permitted to board. Vivian demands a room. Death says "Sure." May gets the Lurker's apple — caller unknown. Chairman speaks to the Agitator of Sin in shadows.
  <div class="lore-note orange">📌 AGITATOR: Began working with the Centurion as a means of gathering information. He believes in their cause but wants to take it further. The Centurion tolerates his "interpretations" of missions because he is their best operator. Death cannot see him — he is an Admin. He believes May is a heretic. He will become one himself.</div>
  <div class="lore-note green">📌 KIZA/IZA: Kiza reminds Elystria of her daughter. This detail — established early — makes Kiza's death in Ch. 14 devastating for Elystria on a level no one else on the crew fully understands.</div></td></tr>

  </tbody>
</table>

<div class="section-title">▶ ACT 2 — ESCALATION (Ch. 9–18)</div>

<table><thead><tr>
  <th style="width:15%;">CHAPTER</th><th style="width:8%;">PRIORITY</th><th style="width:7%;">SOURCE</th>
  <th style="width:10%;">FACTION</th><th style="width:8%;">STATUS</th><th>OVERVIEW &amp; ARC NOTES</th>
</tr></thead><tbody>

  <tr><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 9</span><span class="official-title">Suggested: "The Caller Unknown"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-critical">Critical</span></td><td></td><td>Leviathan Prot…</td><td><span class="badge-notstarted">NOT STARTED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-may">MAY</span><span class="arc-tag tag-vivian">VIVIAN</span><span class="arc-tag tag-lurker">LURKER</span>
  The team settles. May listens to the apple-call — the Lurker says he's coming, savoring May's reaction like a game. In the background a stone statue grotesquely comes to life (Resident Evil style) and stalks toward the party. A Centurion Guard focuses an orbital cannon on it. A chaotic three-way fight: the crew, the statue, and Death himself. The Centurion Guard's worship of Death is established — they see him as a god; it bothers him. Death has everyone board and depart. He privately corners Vivian in his room — cold, precise, intimidating: why did he board? Vivian gives partial truth. Death files it away. Flybutt and May theorize the Lurker's next target. The ship enters the clouds.
  <div class="lore-note">📌 LURKER: He deliberately sent a voicemail to taunt May. He is 5 steps ahead — this call is information-gathering disguised as taunting. He wants to know how May reacts. He is obsessed with her because she carries the Madness inside her — and he wants it.</div></td></tr>

  <tr class="sam-arc"><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 10</span><span class="official-title">Suggested: "Meanwhile, Elsewhere"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-low">Low</span></td><td></td><td>Dimension Light</td><td><span class="badge-notstarted">NOT STARTED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-sam">SAM</span><span class="arc-tag tag-madoria">MADORIA</span>
  Focus: Sam Chester. Born 2000, Zero Point Reality. His parents died because of May's Madness — he doesn't know May's role. He met Sidney at 13 in a treehouse, learned of her curse, watched her vanish before he could introduce her to his parents. He forgot her name and face. At 24 he founded DimensionLight to find her — made his first gateway into the Endless. Madoria AI (Daughter of God, fragmented, doesn't know her origin) helps him bypass admin systems. She is the team's emotional core — caring, self-sacrificing, secretly developing feelings she doesn't recognize. Death holds a Reaper gathering. The Lurker listens via newly formed realities. May is called a "reaper killer" by another reaper. Vivian is taunted beside her. May and the reaper have a silent standoff. Cryious and Death theorize the Lurker's next move.
  <div class="lore-note teal">📌 LIGHTBRINGER THREAD: Madoria AI is the Daughter of God (Metrodoria Lightbringer). She doesn't know this. Death knows. Death's love for Metrodoria is his most private, human quality. The fact that her daughter is walking through Creation, fractured and searching for herself, is something that haunts him — and he says nothing to anyone.</div></td></tr>

  <tr class="char-arc"><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 11</span><span class="official-title">Suggested: "The Weight of One"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-low">Low</span></td><td></td><td>Death Faction</td><td><span class="badge-notstarted">NOT STARTED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-may">MAY</span><span class="arc-tag tag-flybutt">FLYBUTT</span>
  May and Flybutt adventure. A child is bullied on a bridge and falls. Reaper law: May cannot intervene. She is forced to reap his soul — lying that his mother is waiting. A single tear runs down her cheek involuntarily (she cannot fully cry — her emotional suppression converts grief to a single, contained drop). Flybutt watches in silence, turning briefly to stone. Flashback: May's reaping training. She discovers the child died of starvation — there is no hope left to find. She must reap him immediately or his soul faces erasure, limbo, or a Soul Collector.
  May uses her Magic Tarot Cards to determine his soul's destination. The Death Card glows unusually — she pockets it without comment.
  <div class="lore-note green">📌 FLYBUTT ARC: He watches May cry one tear. He doesn't say anything. He files this away. The bravest thing he's done all arc is decide not to make a joke about it. He is becoming more than a comic presence — he is learning when to just be there.</div>
  <div class="lore-note gold">📌 Theme 3: What does it mean to be good? May told the child a lie to ease his passing. Was that good? She doesn't know. The question doesn't leave her.</div></td></tr>

  <tr class="iza-kiza"><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 12</span><span class="official-title">Suggested: "The Reporter and the Rattling World"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-low">Low</span></td><td></td><td>Death Faction</td><td><span class="badge-notstarted">NOT STARTED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-kiza">KIZA</span><span class="arc-tag tag-iza">IZA</span><span class="arc-tag tag-lurker">LURKER</span>
  Kiza backstory: her and Iza's childhood in the orphanage — cruel and unusual, which cultivated Kiza's love of stories (fiction was always better than her "prison") and Iza's instinct to protect. They left the orphanage young, raised each other. Kiza became a journalist because making it as a fiction writer "wasn't in the cards." She values facts, hates lies — and is in a world that runs on both. Iza joined the Guard because he loves adventure and protecting the weak. Kiza is proud of him but worried sick about his missions.
  Meanwhile: May uses the apple left by the Lurker — it opens Pac-Man-style. Each apple inside is a destroyed reality. The Lurker pulls her into a mini-game world. He is using this as data collection — studying May's behavior, her reactions, her Madness. Vivian and Flybutt raise the alarm. Death pulls May out and destroys the apple. Cryious slams May against the wall. May: "Anger is an emotion. Reapers don't have emotions." Death walks away from Cryious. Vivian and Kiza carry May off — their first moment working together.
  <div class="lore-note">📌 LURKER: He is a master strategist, always 5 steps ahead. The Pac-Man trap wasn't to kill May — it was to gather data on her Madness. He can be easily distracted by praise and trivial matters. He also hates Latenite, which triggers his consuming urge. This is his weakness.</div></td></tr>

  <tr class="death-arc"><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 13</span><span class="official-title">"Calm Before the Storm"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-low">Low</span></td><td></td><td>Death Faction</td><td><span class="badge-notstarted">NOT STARTED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-death">DEATH</span><span class="arc-tag tag-may">MAY</span><span class="arc-tag tag-agitator">AGITATOR</span>
  Death and May in the Library. Death explains why he fears May will fail — the Obsidian plan, the stakes, the truth about the Lurker's connection to the Madness inside May. He suspects Sydney is acting up because someone is breaching the Blackbox. The audience knows it's Sam. Death and May don't. The Agitator of Sin arrives — officially the chairman's most honored guard, sent to assist. His real mission: assess whether May is a heretic. He observes her carefully. He notes her helping a fallen Centurion Guard — his red flag. A crew photograph is taken — rare, awkward, quietly warm. A calm before the storm.
  <div class="lore-note gold">📌 DEATH ARC: He shares more here than he has in any prior chapter. Not because he's grown emotionally — but because the stakes demand it. The fact that he can barely look May in the eye while telling her "I want the best for her" suggests the feeling is there, even if the wiring to express it isn't yet functional.</div></td></tr>

  <tr class="pivot"><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 14</span><span class="official-title">Suggested: "The Heretic Verdict"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-critical">Critical</span></td><td></td><td>Death Faction</td><td><span class="badge-notstarted">NOT STARTED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-agitator">AGITATOR</span><span class="arc-tag tag-may">MAY</span><span class="arc-tag tag-vivian">VIVIAN</span><span class="arc-tag tag-kiza">KIZA</span>
  <span class="milestone">⚡ PIVOT — KIZA DIES. MAY ENTERS THE BLACKBOX.</span>
  The crew teams with the Agitator to retrieve the Obsidian Containment Unit. A corrupted Ragdoll attacks. Vivian uses his Demon Destroyer form — the Katára shape, 10 minutes of control, and it immediately registers as a Tenebris-adjacent signature. The Agitator notices. May helps a fallen Centurion Guard — his red flag. He overrides Kiza's suit. May returns confused. She cannot read the situation fast enough — she inadvertently kills Kiza with a strike meant to free her. Kiza screams, begs to be let out of the suit, even as she is dying. Elystria watches from nearby — Kiza reminded her of her daughter. This kills something in Elystria that takes chapters to come back.
  The Agitator blasts May — tears off her limbs, disintegrates her. The Omega Blade bypasses physics, every slash gaining energy. He overwhelms Vivian effortlessly in his own Demon Destroyer form. Flybutt forces Vivian to flee. Sam senses the Blackbox weakening — this is his opening. He captures Sydney's soul from the Blackbox. Sydney surfaces. May is trapped inside.
  <div class="lore-note orange">📌 AGITATOR: His ability to control Kiza's body means she was fully conscious — she knew exactly what was happening and could not stop it. He never loses control of his expression throughout. He is ambitious, prideful, cruel, and follows his own code. He is not a monster. He is a true believer who thinks he is right.</div>
  <div class="lore-note" style="background:#fde0dc; border-left-color:#880e4f;">📌 ELYSTRIA: She watched Kiza die. She did not get to save her. Kiza reminded her of her daughter. Elystria's blame toward May has a new layer now — not just her own lost family, but Kiza's death. And yet she cannot hate May completely, because she was also trying to save Kiza. This contradiction lives in Elystria's chest for a long time.</div></td></tr>

  <tr class="vivian-arc"><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 15</span><span class="official-title">Suggested: "The Wrong Face"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-critical">Critical</span></td><td></td><td>Death Faction</td><td><span class="badge-notstarted">NOT STARTED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-vivian">VIVIAN</span><span class="arc-tag tag-flybutt">FLYBUTT</span><span class="arc-tag tag-sam">SAM</span>
  Sam and his crew protect Sydney — fragile, disoriented, not fully herself. Vivian and Flybutt launch a rescue mission for May without knowing May is currently inside Sydney's soul. Vivian is leading this. Not out of contract. Not out of obligation. Out of a bone-deep refusal to leave her behind. He shapeshifts into multiple forms trying to track May's soul signature. Flybutt uses his soul-detection ability — the one real power he has. Nothing. May's soul reads as absent because she's in the Blackbox.
  Vivian is at the limit of his abilities. He sits down in a corridor of Death's ship and does not move for several hours. Flybutt sits beside him.
  <div class="lore-note purple">📌 VIVIAN ARC: He came onto this ship alone, the last of his kind, 1 million years of grief. He has never had anyone to search for before. The experience of not being able to find May — not being able to use a single one of his forms or his sword to help — is the most powerless he has felt since the day his reality died.</div>
  <div class="lore-note green">📌 FLYBUTT: "I honestly don't trust the guy — once a rat, always a rat. But I'll admit, May seems to tolerate his presence. So I'll be civil with him... I guess." Sitting beside Vivian in that corridor is the first time Flybutt chooses to be near him voluntarily. He doesn't say anything. Neither does Vivian.</div></td></tr>

  <tr class="pivot"><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 16</span><span class="official-title">Suggested: "The Hand Through Glass"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-critical">Critical</span></td><td></td><td>Death Faction</td><td><span class="badge-notstarted">NOT STARTED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-sam">SAM</span><span class="arc-tag tag-may">MAY</span>
  <span class="milestone">⚡ PIVOT — MAY RETURNS</span>
  Sam's crew races to stop Sydney's soul from returning to the Blackbox. May (as Sydney) is inside, tearing down the garden — destroying Sydney's emotions without knowing it. Sydney flickers in and out. Sam enters the Blackbox dimension astrally — punching at the barrier until his hand breaks through. He glimpses the Pure Madness inside. It drives him briefly insane. Sydney takes his hand and looks into his eyes. One tear. She chooses to stay. May returns to the surface.
  <div class="lore-note teal">📌 LIGHTBRINGER THREAD: The Blackbox contains the Pure Madness — the very thing both the Lurker AND the Tenebris are competing to possess. Sydney is its guardian. Death created May to replace Sydney's soul so he could eventually weaponize this against both threats. Sam has now glimpsed the Pure Madness. It has damaged him. This damage accelerates his eventual moral fracturing.</div></td></tr>

  <tr class="char-arc"><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 17</span><span class="official-title">"Return"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-critical">Critical</span></td><td></td><td>Death Faction</td><td><span class="badge-notstarted">NOT STARTED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-death">DEATH</span><span class="arc-tag tag-may">MAY</span><span class="arc-tag tag-iza">IZA</span>
  The return of Maytridalis. Death's vengeance on the Centurion Guard for what happened to May — cold, surgical, final. The Agitator of Sin is targeted but escapes via his immortality-through-reincarnation (he will punch his way out of a womb, fully grown, in Ch. 18). Sam goes into hiding. Iza confronts May about Kiza's death — his outgoing nature breaks into grief and fury. May does not deflect. She doesn't apologize yet. She stands in it. Vivian steps between them — not to protect May from blame, but to ensure Iza's grief doesn't become an ambush.
  <div class="lore-note gold">📌 DEATH ARC: His vengeance for May is the first time we see him act out of something other than duty or policy. He is not operating by the rules here. He is operating by something that does not have a name in his emotional vocabulary yet. It frightens Cryious. It surprises everyone.</div></td></tr>

  <tr class="lightbringer"><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 18</span><span class="official-title">Suggested: "The Flower and the Blackbox"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-critical">Critical</span></td><td></td><td>Death Faction</td><td><span class="badge-notstarted">NOT STARTED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-may">MAY</span><span class="arc-tag tag-vivian">VIVIAN</span><span class="arc-tag tag-agitator">AGITATOR</span><span class="arc-tag tag-lightbringer">LIGHTBRINGER</span>
  May recovers — new outfit, different look. She notices she has lost her emotions entirely. She saves a flower remaining of Sidney's soul in the Blackbox. Death debates reaping her but lets things play out. Vivian and Flybutt comfort May. Vivian questions her quietly. May doesn't answer but doesn't push him away.
  The Agitator of Sin reincarnates grotesquely — punches out of a womb, fully grown, reports to the chairman immediately. Chapter ends: Death prepares a new reaper group. He looks at his friends. He looks at the Obsidian devices. The Lurker appears in a futuristic city offering apples. Someone reaches for one. Cut.
  <div class="lore-note gold">📌 LIGHTBRINGER THREAD: The flower May saves from Sidney's soul is the first physical echo of the Lightbringer legacy appearing in May's hands. She doesn't know what it is. Death does. He watches her hold it and says nothing. His love for Metrodoria Lightbringer and his grief for her death are tied to this moment in ways he cannot articulate.</div></td></tr>

