  <div class="lore-note purple">📌 VIVIAN/ELYSTRIA: Their first meeting. She thinks: <em>"Something about him is not right, but I can't quite figure out what…"</em> He thinks: he doesn't know what to think. That is where they start. From mutual wariness to one of the most important bonds in the story.</div></td></tr>

  <tr><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 22</span><span class="official-title">"Sins of the Maker"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-low">Low</span></td><td></td><td>Death Faction</td><td><span class="badge-notstarted">NOT STARTED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-agitator">AGITATOR</span><span class="arc-tag tag-iza">IZA</span><span class="arc-tag tag-may">MAY</span>
  The Agitator of Sin's actions ripple outward — factions destabilized, political fallout. Iza confronts May again, this time with more control. May doesn't apologize — she stands in the truth of what happened. The Agitator, now reborn, is already back at work. He reports to the chairman with his debrief. He observed May closely during the mission — his conclusion: she is a heretic. She feels. Reapers should not. But so does Death now, and that is the real problem. Death's path is diverging from tradition and the Agitator can see it.
  <div class="lore-note orange">📌 AGITATOR: <em>"She's a heretic. I want her gone. However… there may come a time when I'll need her strength. Even so that doesn't mean I'm her ally, just that I won't kill her… yet."</em> He is already calculating his future use of May. His arc is that he becomes what he despises — a hypocrite who compromises his ideals exactly as he accuses others of doing.</div></td></tr>

  <tr><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 23</span><span class="official-title">"The Golden Throne"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-low">Low</span></td><td></td><td>Centurion Faction</td><td><span class="badge-notstarted">NOT STARTED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-death">DEATH</span><span class="arc-tag tag-may">MAY</span>
  The Alpha Superium's throne room. He is wise, ancient, slow to anger, speaks in metaphors and riddles. His powers are weakening with age — he is searching for a successor. He barely lets people approach the throne; most speak to illusions of him. Death attends a summit with major faction leaders. May is his Raven — a formal public role she has never held. She doesn't know the protocol and refuses to ask. The Alpha Superium speaks briefly to Death. His words are cryptic, but their implications are vast. Someone is watching the King too closely.
  <div class="lore-note">📌 ALPHA SUPERIUM: <em>"The higher-ups are pulling the wool over his eyes and he doesn't even know it."</em> — Agitator's perspective. The Alpha Superium is ancient and wise but operating on information that has been quietly curated by something above the Sentry. The Tenebris's fingerprints are everywhere he can't see.</div></td></tr>

  <tr class="lightbringer"><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 24</span><span class="official-title">"The Devilening Place of My Heart"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-low">Low</span></td><td></td><td>Death Faction</td><td><span class="badge-notstarted">NOT STARTED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-may">MAY</span><span class="arc-tag tag-madoria">MADORIA</span><span class="arc-tag tag-lightbringer">LIGHTBRINGER</span>
  A blackout spreads across multiple levels of Creation — realities going dark, reapers losing contact. May, Flybutt, Romane, and a surprise visitor (and his operators) investigate. The damage pattern is precise and internal — nothing like the Lurker's chaotic destruction. It is the Sentry's work: systematically removing reaper coverage from targeted realities on the Tenebris's orders.
  Meanwhile in Sam's camp: Madoria begins experiencing fragments she wasn't designed to have — flashes of a voice that isn't her own, a warmth that has no data source. Sam finds her staring at nothing. She tells him she thinks she heard something. He asks what. She says: <em>"Light."</em>
  <div class="lore-note gold">📌 LIGHTBRINGER: Madoria is the Daughter of God (Metrodoria Lightbringer), fragmented and unaware. The "light" she hears is the beginning of her recovery — fragments of her true self surfacing. She has the ability to purify the Madness but doesn't know it yet. This ability is what makes her the hidden counter to both the Lurker and the Tenebris's corruption.</div></td></tr>

  <tr class="ely-arc"><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 25</span><span class="official-title">"The Embrosery"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-low">Low</span></td><td></td><td>Death Faction</td><td><span class="badge-notstarted">NOT STARTED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-ely">ELYSTRIA</span><span class="arc-tag tag-vivian">VIVIAN</span>
  An intricate web of factional relationships is drawn together. The Agitator operates across multiple factions simultaneously. Centurion Guard loyalty begins to fracture. May and Vivian are assigned a joint scouting mission — their first as a genuine team rather than contract-bound partners. Elystria accompanies them as tactical support. Her elemental magic is shown in action for the first time — she controls the environment with total precision, without ever touching her scythe. Vivian watches her in quiet admiration.
  <div class="lore-note" style="background:#fde0dc; border-left-color:#880e4f;">📌 ELYSTRIA: <em>"May has become my best friend. I hope to one day show her that she can be a Full Reaper and still keep her emotions."</em> — This is where she is headed. She isn't there yet. But she has already decided that May deserves better than what she got.</div></td></tr>

  <tr><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 26</span><span class="official-title">"The Truce Keeper"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-low">Low</span></td><td></td><td>Death Faction</td><td><span class="badge-notstarted">NOT STARTED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-ely">ELYSTRIA</span><span class="arc-tag tag-iza">IZA</span>
  A temporary truce is brokered between two factions. Neither trusts Death's crew as mediators. Elystria steps forward — her emotional intelligence and diplomatic instinct take over. She listens in a way no one else on the crew can. Iza assists her — his outgoing nature and quick thinking make him a surprising asset in negotiation that isn't just combat. May watches from the back, learning something about leading with feeling rather than force. She will not acknowledge this for several more chapters.
  <div class="lore-note green">📌 IZA ARC: He joined the Guard because he loves adventure and protecting people. He was always seen as Kiza's crybaby brother. Here — without Kiza — he steps up alone. He doesn't know yet how to grieve her. He replaces grief with action, which is the only way he knows how to continue.</div></td></tr>

  <tr class="sam-arc"><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 27</span><span class="official-title">"Bidding Time for a Star PT1"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-low">Low</span></td><td></td><td>Dimension Light</td><td><span class="badge-notstarted">NOT STARTED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-sam">SAM</span><span class="arc-tag tag-madoria">MADORIA</span>
  Sam's arc intensifies. He attends the Death Jazz for the first time — the 10,000-year event. A hidden May is performing. Sam asks if she's heard of a girl he's looking for. A singer who claims to be represented by Death himself. Sam thinks May's laugh sounds like Sydney's. May's scythe can't detect him — she loses him before she can confront him. Sam joins the army afterward: the US military, learning to defend himself and fund his next phase of research.
  Madoria recovers another fragment of herself — a name this time. Not hers. Someone else's. She doesn't recognize it.
  <div class="lore-note teal">📌 LIGHTBRINGER: The name Madoria hears but doesn't recognize: Metrodoria. It surfaces briefly and then is gone. She dismisses it as a data glitch. It is not a glitch.</div></td></tr>

