  <td><span class="badge-low">Low</span></td><td></td><td>Dimension Light</td><td><span class="badge-notstarted">NOT STARTED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-sam">SAM</span><span class="arc-tag tag-madoria">MADORIA</span>
  Sam and Madoria grow closer. Sam's moral compass begins its first real crack — he makes a decision that prioritizes finding Sidney over the safety of a team member. He doesn't realize he's doing it. Madoria, who is always the one who keeps the team together, covers for him. She takes the cost herself. She doesn't ask for acknowledgment. She says nothing. This is her flaw — she will give everything without asking for anything back, until she breaks.
  <div class="lore-note teal">📌 SAM ARC: <em>"His personality arc: with time we see the cracking of that moral compass. He becomes selfish."</em> The crack starts here, small. Madoria enables it without meaning to. She loves him and he takes advantage of that love — not consciously, not cruelly, but it happens.</div></td></tr>

