  Sam returns to his original reality. His complex is burning. His best friend Arline apologizes for not being ready. The US general pulls their funding. Sam watches the Lurker appear — looking like a fading memory — and tell him everything about May, about Sidney being a soul in a far-away place, about the reality bomb having killed him. Sam decides to accept the lie that Sidney was never real. He moves on. Accepts it. Even though he knows it's a lie.
