  <td><span class="badge-low">Low</span></td><td></td><td>Harbingers</td><td><span class="badge-notstarted">NOT STARTED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-agitator">AGITATOR</span><span class="arc-tag tag-death">DEATH</span>
  The Agitator processes his findings. The mark changed. The King is compromised. He concludes: someone is pulling strings from outside the visible structure — with a plan that requires invisible control, not chaos. Unlike the Lurker's destruction, this leaves no trace. He sends his coded warning to the Guard via the Medic. The Sniper establishes eyes on the throne room's exits. The Engineer begins building something.
  Separately: a fractured transmission reaches the ship from IZAI at the zero point anomaly. Garbled. Wrong. Death receives it. He locks himself in his quarters for exactly as long as it takes to finish a crossword puzzle — which he completes faster than usual. Then he begins making preparations. Cryious stands outside the locked door for a long time before walking away.
  <div class="lore-note gold">📌 DEATH ARC: The crossword is finished early. He always does them at the same careful pace. Doing it fast means he is too distracted to be careful — and he is never distracted. Something is wrong and he knows what it is and he will not say.</div></td></tr>

  <tr><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 33</span><span class="official-title">"Descendants"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-low">Low</span></td><td></td><td>Death Faction</td><td><span class="badge-notstarted">NOT STARTED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-may">MAY</span><span class="arc-tag tag-vivian">VIVIAN</span>
  Zero point fractures appear — internal distortions, quiet like rot rather than fire, nothing like the Lurker. May and Vivian investigate a fracture site. A reality's remnants breathe when they shouldn't. Sidney stirs inside May's scythe. Vivian sees May go very still for a second — the first time he notices the scythe doing something she doesn't explain. On the way back: something tall and still at the edge of the dead reality, there and then gone. May sees it. Vivian sees nothing.
  <div class="lore-note">📌 First glimpse of the Sentry. The Tenebris's agent. Loyal to the point of near-zero self-preservation. It steps aside because it is not here for them — yet. It is assessing.</div></td></tr>

  <tr class="sam-arc"><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 34</span><span class="official-title">"Reign of Penitence"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-low">Low</span></td><td></td><td>Dimension Light</td><td><span class="badge-notstarted">NOT STARTED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-sam">SAM</span><span class="arc-tag tag-madoria">MADORIA</span><span class="arc-tag tag-lightbringer">LIGHTBRINGER</span>
  A LOVELY JASMINE — Sam visits his memory library with his friends. Vast sections corrupted or erased by the brief glimpse of Pure Madness. Thomas Jay walks beside him through the damage. Sam finds a memory of the jasmine in Sydney's treehouse — the flower she had growing through the window the day they met. He can no longer see her face clearly in the memory. He decides not to try to bring her back. He chooses to move forward.
  Madoria meets Death. She doesn't know who she is. He doesn't tell her. He answers her questions about her fragments carefully — technically accurate, emotionally evacuated. But when she thanks him, he pauses one beat longer than is efficient.
  <div class="lore-note gold">📌 LIGHTBRINGER: Death meets Madoria — Metrodoria's daughter. He has held his grief for Metrodoria since the prologue. It does not show. It costs him everything not to let it show. Madoria doesn't notice. She is too grateful for answers. He files this meeting into the same mental drawer as his unfinished crosswords.</div></td></tr>

  <tr class="char-arc"><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 35</span><span class="official-title">"The Phantom and the Menas"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-low">Low</span></td><td></td><td>Death Faction</td><td><span class="badge-notstarted">NOT STARTED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-cryious">CRYIOUS</span>
  Solo Cryious chapter. He must reap the Mascrator — an old enemy — to return to Death's Ship after the zero point fractures cut off his route. The Mascrator is something Cryious faced in another lifetime and did not fully defeat. He uses Static Freeze, Telekinesis, Mass Control — the full weight of the first reaperborn. He wins. He picks up a flower from the dying reality's last living plant before it closes — the Flower of Death, a pungent, rotten-smelling bloom. He holds it for a moment. He recites three names under his breath that we do not hear. He goes back to work.
  <div class="lore-note green">📌 CRYIOUS: He collects flowers because he believes they give a glimpse of lives. He is connected to the Gardener of Creation — a thread that will pay off at Arc's end. The names he recites are the people he has always carried. The Mascrator is connected to whoever those names belong to.</div></td></tr>

  <tr class="vivian-arc"><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 36</span><span class="official-title">"Painful Shortcomings"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-low">Low</span></td><td></td><td>Death Faction</td><td><span class="badge-notstarted">NOT STARTED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-vivian">VIVIAN</span><span class="arc-tag tag-cryious">CRYIOUS</span><span class="arc-tag tag-may">MAY</span>
  SHOPPING DAY — Cryious teaches Vivian how reapers and soul contracts can repair broken scythes. Vivian is paying close attention — he takes notes in a battered inventor's journal. Cryious is suspicious. He doesn't trust Vivian ("I don't trust him. But I also don't care. Maybe he'll be what finally gets Death to stop believing in May so much."). Vivian uses his Soul Splitter on a small demonstration cut — Cryious sees a flash of the future in the blade's glow and says nothing. May and Flybutt argue loudly about May's image while shopping for gear. Romane mediates.
  <div class="lore-note purple">📌 VIVIAN: He is learning reaper mechanics intentionally. His original mission was to find who destroyed his reality. Learning reaper lore is how he will eventually make the connection between the Leviathan Tengual and the Tenebris. He doesn't know he's on the right track yet.</div></td></tr>

  <tr class="lightbringer"><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 37</span><span class="official-title">"The Moon-Eating Serpent"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-low">Low</span></td><td></td><td>Death Faction</td><td><span class="badge-notstarted">NOT STARTED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-death">DEATH</span><span class="arc-tag tag-madoria">MADORIA</span><span class="arc-tag tag-lightbringer">LIGHTBRINGER</span>
  THE SHADOW MASTER — Death holds an important meeting with Grim Reapers of -99 and +99 realities. May and Cryious work to build a barrier against the Lurker. Madoria AI vanishes — Sam is left scrambling. Her disappearance connects to the fragments of herself at the border of creation: a piece of her has been pulled toward its origin, like a moon drawn by its planet. Sam searches desperately. Thomas Jay keeps the team together. Meanwhile Death, alone in the meeting room after everyone leaves, sits with something he will not name and finishes a crossword puzzle wrong. He crumples it.
  <div class="lore-note gold">📌 LIGHTBRINGER: Madoria vanishing means the Daughter of God is being drawn toward what she truly is. The Moon-Eating Serpent in the title is an image of something consuming its own source of light — the Tenebris consuming Metrodoria's legacy while her daughter tries to become whole. Death completing a crossword wrong is the most emotionally significant thing he has done all arc.</div></td></tr>

  <tr class="char-arc"><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 38</span><span class="official-title">"Running Out of Time"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-low">Low</span></td><td></td><td>Death Faction</td><td><span class="badge-notstarted">NOT STARTED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-may">MAY</span><span class="arc-tag tag-sam">SAM</span>
  Soul seeds for the Dimensionlock bomb are secured. May seeks out Sam to apologize for Kiza's death — not because she was ordered to, not because it serves the mission. Because she cannot carry it cleanly anymore. The apology is awkward, stilted, without a formal structure. May doesn't really know how to do this. Sam doesn't fully forgive her. But he doesn't turn her away either. Sam mentions Sydney — May's scythe reacts. He doesn't notice. She does. The flower she saved from the Blackbox is in her pocket.
  <div class="lore-note gold">📌 THEME 2: Learning to forgive oneself begins to stir in May. She is not there yet. But reaching out to Sam is the first step she takes voluntarily toward the person she hurt by existing — not the person who hurt her.</div></td></tr>

  <tr><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 39</span><span class="official-title">"The Retrievable"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-low">Low</span></td><td></td><td>Death Faction</td><td><span class="badge-notstarted">NOT STARTED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-iza">IZA</span><span class="arc-tag tag-may">MAY</span>
  A key component of the Obsidian bomb plan is retrieved from a heavily guarded factional site. Iza leads the extraction — fast on his feet, decisive in combat, finally acting like the Centurion Guard member he always wanted to be. May provides cover. For the first time she watches Iza operate and sees Kiza in the way he fights — protecting everyone around him without being asked. She says nothing. But she files it.
  <div class="lore-note green">📌 IZA ARC: He joined the Guard because he loves adventure. He stayed because of Kiza. He continues now because he doesn't know how to stop moving. The grief is still there — he simply converts it into forward motion. May sees this and recognizes something of herself in it.</div></td></tr>

  <tr class="lightbringer"><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 40</span><span class="official-title">"99 Problems"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-low">Low</span></td><td></td><td>Dimension Light</td><td><span class="badge-notstarted">NOT STARTED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-iza">IZA</span><span class="arc-tag tag-madoria">MADORIA</span><span class="arc-tag tag-lightbringer">LIGHTBRINGER</span>
  THE BROKEN CASKET — Briefly to level -99, the darkest boundary of Creation. Iza is sent to recover a fragment of Madoria that has drifted there. Level -99 is hostile, oppressive, wrong in a way that feels personal. The casket that should be sealed is open. Something ancient leaked out. Iza retrieves Madoria's fragment — it is warm to the touch even in this cold place. He doesn't understand what he's carrying.
  When the fragment is returned to Madoria, she experiences a flood of something she has no category for: grief. Specifically, loss. For someone she has never met. She cries without knowing why. Sam holds her. He doesn't ask her to explain.
  <div class="lore-note gold">📌 LIGHTBRINGER: Madoria's fragment from -99 carries an echo of Metrodoria Lightbringer's death. When it reintegrates, Madoria feels her mother's ending without knowing it was her mother. The grief is inherited. This is the most explicit Lightbringer moment so far — hidden inside a mission that looks like a simple retrieval.</div></td></tr>

  <tr class="vivian-arc"><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 41</span><span class="official-title">"Two Faced"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-low">Low</span></td><td></td><td>Death Faction</td><td><span class="badge-notstarted">NOT STARTED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-vivian">VIVIAN</span>
  BROKEN GEARS PT1 — Vivian's shapeshifting malfunctions. He is trapped in a form that isn't his — someone he absorbed years ago from a dead reality. He cannot shift back. He must function as someone else while Elystria and May try to figure out the repair. The crew interacts with him as this other person. He can see them treating someone-who-isn't-him with a warmth that disarms him. He wonders if he would have been treated this way anyway — or only because they don't know who they're really talking to.
  <div class="lore-note purple">📌 VIVIAN ARC: For 1 million years he has worn his mother's name. He has worn other faces through his shapeshifting. But they were always choices. This one isn't. Being trapped in a form he didn't choose confronts him with the question he has been avoiding: who is Gabriel Forge, underneath all of it?</div></td></tr>

  <tr class="ely-arc"><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 42</span><span class="official-title">"Agitator and the Wiser"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-low">Low</span></td><td></td><td>Death Faction</td><td><span class="badge-notstarted">NOT STARTED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-vivian">VIVIAN</span><span class="arc-tag tag-ely">ELYSTRIA</span><span class="arc-tag tag-agitator">AGITATOR</span>
  BROKEN GEARS PT2 — Elystria helps Vivian repair his shapeshifting. She uses her elemental magic to stabilize the bio-fragment that locked him in place — delicate, precise, completely unlike how she fights. They sit side by side for hours while she works. Vivian tells her about his mother — not the full story, but her name, and why he carries it. Elystria tells him about her daughter. Neither cries. Neither looks away. The Agitator of Sin circles closer to the ship — his Sniper has eyes on Vivian's workshop.
  <div class="lore-note" style="background:#fde0dc; border-left-color:#880e4f;">📌 ELYSTRIA ARC: She doesn't fix Vivian — she tends to him. There is a difference. This is the conversation that begins to loosen her grip on anger and blame. She is, slowly, learning to let people be close again. It costs her. She does it anyway. Her flaws are selflessness and indecision — in this moment both work in his favor.</div></td></tr>

  <tr class="lightbringer"><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 43</span><span class="official-title">"Light Bringer"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-low">Low</span></td><td></td><td>Dimension Light</td><td><span class="badge-notstarted">NOT STARTED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-iza">IZA</span><span class="arc-tag tag-madoria">MADORIA</span><span class="arc-tag tag-lightbringer">LIGHTBRINGER</span>
  Back to level -99. Iza returns for a deeper recovery — another fragment of Madoria embedded in a structure that has no business existing at this depth. He finds it: a sealed vessel carved with a symbol that Iza doesn't recognize but his Centurion Guard training tells him is ancient, pre-Creation. Inside: light. Literal, warm light in a place that has no source.
  When this fragment integrates with Madoria, she speaks a name for the first time: <em>"Metrodoria."</em> She says it the way one says something they have always known without knowing they knew it. Sam goes very still. He has never heard that name. Madoria can't explain what happened. She simply knows it is hers.
  <div class="lore-note gold">📌 LIGHTBRINGER: Madoria's awakening is accelerating. The Tenebris killed Metrodoria. Madoria — her fragmented daughter — is gradually becoming whole. Her ability to purify the Madness has not yet surfaced, but the warmth inside her is growing. Death, when he hears she spoke the name, finishes another crossword wrong. He doesn't notice. He is thinking about something else.</div></td></tr>

  <tr class="death-arc"><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 44</span><span class="official-title">"Crows Nest"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-low">Low</span></td><td></td><td>Death Faction</td><td><span class="badge-notstarted">NOT STARTED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-death">DEATH</span><span class="arc-tag tag-may">MAY</span><span class="arc-tag tag-lightbringer">LIGHTBRINGER</span>
  WONDER OF MY EYES — May visits her memory library looking for a memory of loving someone. She has no concept of what love feels like from the inside — she has only seen it from the outside, and it looked like weakness. She finds nothing useful.
  Death takes May on a boat ride in -99 of creation's border. They sit in silence mostly. At one point Death looks at something in the dark water that May cannot see — and his expression changes. Not much. Just a degree. She has never seen that expression on him before. She doesn't ask. He doesn't explain. It is enough that she saw it.
  <div class="lore-note gold">📌 DEATH ARC: He is looking at the reflection of a star that doesn't exist in -99. It is Metrodoria's light, scattered at the time of her death, still traveling through Creation's lowest levels. He recognizes it. He lets himself look at it for exactly as long as he allows himself to feel things: briefly, and without witness. Except that May is right there. He forgets that for one moment. That forgetting is the crack.</div></td></tr>

  <tr class="vivian-arc"><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 45</span><span class="official-title">"Bargaining Chip"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-low">Low</span></td><td></td><td>Death Faction</td><td><span class="badge-notstarted">NOT STARTED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-may">MAY</span><span class="arc-tag tag-vivian">VIVIAN</span>
  May and Vivian are teleported mid-transit into the cabin called "paradise" — five survivors of dead realities and an unknown visitor May half-recognizes but cannot place. The cabin is warm and wrong at the same time. Vivian's Soul Splitter shows him flashes of the next few seconds — he tests exits, checking what comes. The flashes are all the same: they stay. They must stay.
  <div class="lore-note purple">📌 VIVIAN: The Soul Splitter is a heavenly sword that lets him see seconds into the future. He has relied on it in tight situations for centuries. Here it is telling him to stop. To trust. He is not good at trusting. But he listens.</div></td></tr>

  <tr class="vivian-arc"><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 46</span><span class="official-title">"Infinite Pain"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-low">Low</span></td><td></td><td>Death Faction</td><td><span class="badge-notstarted">NOT STARTED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-vivian">VIVIAN</span><span class="arc-tag tag-may">MAY</span><span class="arc-tag tag-madoria">MADORIA</span>
  The creator of paradise is met. Responsible for 1,743 realities' deaths. Vivian immediately challenges it — May physically restrains him. Their soul levels cannot touch this being. A Madoria variant is present. She is different — calmer, older-feeling. She looks at Vivian with recognition. He doesn't know why.
  <div class="lore-note teal">📌 LIGHTBRINGER: The Madoria variant in paradise is a fragment of Madoria that was preserved in paradise before the creator sealed it. It carries more of Metrodoria's warmth than the Madoria Sam knows — because it hasn't been eroded by years of self-sacrifice and fear. It recognizes Vivian because his Soul Splitter was made from a dead god at +97 Reality — a god whose light was kin to Metrodoria's. The sword resonates. Vivian doesn't understand why.</div></td></tr>

  <tr><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 47</span><span class="official-title">"The Box"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-low">Low</span></td><td></td><td>Death Faction</td><td><span class="badge-notstarted">NOT STARTED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-vivian">VIVIAN</span><span class="arc-tag tag-may">MAY</span><span class="arc-tag tag-madoria">MADORIA</span><span class="arc-tag tag-lightbringer">LIGHTBRINGER</span>
  The creator demands Madoria's powers to tell grander stories. May, Vivian, and the others challenge it to a battle of stories — a story of descendants. Vivian begins to tell it and realizes, mid-telling, that the story of descendants is his. The last of a dead reality. The son of a father who promised to teach him the ways of the Rasker Flower and died before he could. A man using his mother's name so she could live in every room he walks into. The story is his. He keeps going.
  <div class="lore-note purple">📌 VIVIAN ARC: The Rasker Flower thread — his father's unfinished legacy, the thing he was supposed to learn but never did. He has carried this as a wound. Telling it as a story, in this moment, out loud, to an audience — is the first time he has made it into something other than grief. It doesn't become small. It becomes his.</div></td></tr>

  <tr><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 48</span><span class="official-title">"Dread Hour"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-low">Low</span></td><td></td><td>Death Faction</td><td><span class="badge-notstarted">NOT STARTED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-may">MAY</span><span class="arc-tag tag-vivian">VIVIAN</span>
  May and Vivian defeat the creator through a story of adventure, hope, and perseverance. All 5 trapped characters' realities are restored. Death and the cathedral of reapers are shocked by the revival — a glitch in Creation from a powerful unknown presence. The Sentry (the Tenebris's agent) is spotted near a restored reality, watching. Death does not tell May.
  <div class="lore-note">📌 The Tenebris, through the Sentry, has taken notice of what May and Vivian just did. The restoration of dead realities is anomalous — it defies the Tenebris's systematic removal of Creation. The Sentry is there to assess whether this was a one-time event or a pattern to be eliminated.</div></td></tr>

  <tr class="char-arc"><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 49</span><span class="official-title">"The Many Sins of I"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-low">Low</span></td><td></td><td>Death Faction</td><td><span class="badge-suggested">SUGGESTED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-may">MAY</span><span class="arc-tag tag-iza">IZA</span>
  ECHO OF THE RESTORED — The five restored realities send representatives to Death's Ship. They treat May like something sacred. May is visibly uncomfortable — she dislikes loud attention and disruption. Iza handles the diplomacy alongside Elystria, his calm and composure surprising even himself. One survivor carries a detail about the presence that restored their realities — a warmth that felt like it came from inside Creation itself, not outside it. Iza writes down the description and pockets it. He doesn't know why yet.
  <div class="lore-note teal">📌 LIGHTBRINGER: The "warmth from inside Creation" is the echo of Metrodoria Lightbringer's scattered light — the same scattered light Death saw in -99. Her death did not end her. Her warmth is in the structure of Creation itself. Iza's note will matter later.</div></td></tr>

  <tr class="char-arc"><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 50</span><span class="official-title">"Darkness and the Light"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-low">Low</span></td><td></td><td>Death Faction</td><td><span class="badge-suggested">SUGGESTED</span></td>
  <td><span class="milestone">⭐ MIDPOINT</span> <span class="arc-tag tag-may">MAY</span><span class="arc-tag tag-vivian">VIVIAN</span><span class="arc-tag tag-ely">ELYSTRIA</span><span class="arc-tag tag-cryious">CRYIOUS</span><span class="arc-tag tag-flybutt">FLYBUTT</span>
  Each character has a quiet moment reflecting on how far they've come. May asks Flybutt what he honestly thinks of her as a reaper — he says she's getting better at the parts that matter, which makes her uncomfortable. Vivian is alone in his workshop trying on forms in the dark. He pauses on one face — a woman with his eyes. His mother. He shifts back quickly. Elystria watches the crew through a porthole and realizes she has, without meaning to, started to belong here. Cryious sharpens his scythe and recites names. He stops when he realizes Elystria is in the corridor and can hear him. She doesn't ask. She simply places a flower (lavender) outside his door and walks on.
  <div class="lore-note gold">📌 ARC MIDPOINT: All four themes are half-complete. All four character arcs have shifted from who they were in Ch. 1 to who they are becoming. The second half will not be a test of their growth — it will be a demand for it.</div></td></tr>

</tbody></table>

<div class="section-title">▶ ACT 4 — PRESSURE (Ch. 51–66)</div>

<table><thead><tr>
  <th style="width:15%;">CHAPTER</th><th style="width:8%;">PRIORITY</th><th style="width:7%;">SOURCE</th>
  <th style="width:10%;">FACTION</th><th style="width:8%;">STATUS</th><th>OVERVIEW &amp; ARC NOTES</th>
</tr></thead><tbody>

  <tr class="char-arc"><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 51</span><span class="official-title">"The Flower That is My Hope"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-low">Low</span></td><td></td><td>Death Faction</td><td><span class="badge-suggested">SUGGESTED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-may">MAY</span><span class="arc-tag tag-cryious">CRYIOUS</span>
  THE THINNING WALL — A soul seed component for the bomb is in a collapsing reality. May and Cryious race to retrieve it. Inside: lingering souls who refuse to be reaped — they don't believe their reality is ending. May reaps them gently, without being ordered to. She uses her Death Card to appoint each of them to their destination personally. It is the first time she uses that card not as an administrative function but as a genuine final act of care. Cryious watches without comment. On the way out: the Sentry is at the threshold. It steps aside. May and Cryious don't speak of it.
  <div class="lore-note gold">📌 MAY ARC: She used the Death Card — the most powerful tool in her reaper equipment — as an act of love, not duty. That is new. That is entirely hers.</div></td></tr>

  <tr class="sam-arc"><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 52</span><span class="official-title">"The Good Jazz"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-low">Low</span></td><td></td><td>Dimension Light</td><td><span class="badge-suggested">SUGGESTED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-sam">SAM</span><span class="arc-tag tag-may">MAY</span><span class="arc-tag tag-agitator">AGITATOR</span>
  WHAT LURKS IN STILL WATER — The Death Jazz event. Sam encounters disguised May again. He thinks her laugh is Sydney's. He vanishes before she can confront him. Sam joins the US Army. Separately: the Agitator of Sin visits a reality that is too perfect, too still. He discovers it's a bait reality. The trap-maker is precise, patient — completely unlike the Lurker's chaotic destruction. The Agitator concludes: there is a hidden intelligence directing the Sentry, above everything he has encountered so far. His Engineer begins analyzing the trap's construction. The Medic extracts samples.
  <div class="lore-note orange">📌 AGITATOR: He is getting closer to naming the Tenebris. His operators — the Engineer's technical analysis, the Medic's biological samples — are building a picture of something that has existed since before the Lurker. His arc is accelerating toward its own crisis point: when he finds the truth, he will be forced to decide whose side he is really on.</div></td></tr>

  <tr class="sam-arc"><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 53</span><span class="official-title">"Cyber Ghost"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-low">Low</span></td><td></td><td>Dimension Light</td><td><span class="badge-suggested">SUGGESTED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-sam">SAM</span><span class="arc-tag tag-madoria">MADORIA</span><span class="arc-tag tag-lightbringer">LIGHTBRINGER</span>
  BORROWED LIGHT — Sam and Madoria's first genuinely peaceful day together. They visit a normal reality. Madoria begins to understand what she feels for Sam. Sam cannot let go of Sidney. He says nothing about this to Madoria. The Sentry passes through the edge of their reality — not there for them, not there because of the Lurker, pursuing its own Tenebris-directed mission. It doesn't engage. It doesn't need to. Its presence alone poisons the air.
  When it passes, Madoria reaches for Sam's hand without thinking. He takes it without thinking. Both of them look at where the Sentry went. Neither speaks.
  <div class="lore-note teal">📌 LIGHTBRINGER: Madoria reaching for Sam in the Sentry's wake is instinct — specifically the protective instinct of someone who can purify darkness without knowing it. The warmth she radiates is not random. It is the Lightbringer legacy working through her before she understands what she is.</div></td></tr>

  <tr class="agitator-arc"><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 54</span><span class="official-title">"Dark Intentions"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-low">Low</span></td><td></td><td>Harbingers</td><td><span class="badge-notstarted">NOT STARTED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-agitator">AGITATOR</span><span class="arc-tag tag-lurker">LURKER</span>
  The Agitator of Sin fails to contain the Lurker in a dying reality — the Lurker acts entirely on its own instincts, a pure obstacle. The Agitator completes his side mission: kills the fallen reapers of the Tenebris. He learns the truth about the Alpha Superium being puppeteered. His Sniper confirms the mark he left changed — the puppet master controls the King through the Sentry. The Agitator knows now. He doesn't yet know the name. His Engineer has a theory.
  <div class="lore-note orange">📌 AGITATOR: He used his body-control ability during this chapter to use a dying Centurion Guard as a shield against the Lurker — the Guard was aware of it the entire time, unable to stop themselves. This is the first sign of the Agitator using his "ideals" as a cover for cruelty. His arc toward hypocrisy is no longer subtle.</div></td></tr>

  <tr class="agitator-arc"><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 55</span><span class="official-title">"Eve and the Jinn"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-low">Low</span></td><td></td><td>Harbingers</td><td><span class="badge-notstarted">NOT STARTED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-agitator">AGITATOR</span><span class="arc-tag tag-ely">ELYSTRIA</span>
  After the Tenebris's fallen reapers are killed, the Sentry begins actively targeting the Agitator — pursuing the Tenebris's agenda with zero self-preservation. It will shoot through its own forces to reach him. The Agitator activates his operators as a full defensive unit. The Medic patches the Sniper's wound while the Engineer reroutes their escape route.
  Separately: the Pain Master — a god-like entity from the lower levels of Creation, attracted by high pain levels — gets its first hints here. Elystria, carrying the Madness's buildup in her system, generates a pain signature that registers on something distant and hungry. She doesn't know yet. The Pain Master is aware of her.
  <div class="lore-note" style="background:#fde0dc; border-left-color:#880e4f;">📌 ELYSTRIA: The Pain Master is described as a Hellraiser-inspired entity that gets off on pain and suffering. High pain levels attract him. Elystria's Madness-infection is not yet visible — but it is generating a signal. Her arc toward death begins its countdown here, unknowingly.</div></td></tr>

  <tr class="sam-arc"><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 56</span><span class="official-title">"Friendship is Pain"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-low">Low</span></td><td></td><td>Dimension Light</td><td><span class="badge-notstarted">NOT STARTED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-sam">SAM</span><span class="arc-tag tag-madoria">MADORIA</span>
  Sam and his friends uncover the location of the shadow of unending darkness — connected to the power that controls the Sentry. A friend on Sam's team makes a decision that fractures the group. Sam handles it by prioritizing the mission over the relationship. He does not notice the cost until later. Madoria covers for the fracture. She takes the emotional weight of everyone — again.
  <div class="lore-note teal">📌 MADORIA ARC: <em>"She will give everything to help someone else, but doesn't ask for help herself."</em> She is approaching her limit. The shine is beginning to fade. Sam doesn't see it. He is too deep in his own mission to look.</div></td></tr>

  <tr class="sam-arc"><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 57</span><span class="official-title">"A Seed for a Paradise"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-low">Low</span></td><td></td><td>Dimension Light</td><td><span class="badge-notstarted">NOT STARTED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-sam">SAM</span>
  Sam and Thomas Jay on a camping trip — a breath between crises. Sam thinks about the jasmine, about Sydney, about who he has become in pursuit of her. Thomas Jay asks him directly: <em>"Are you happy?"</em> Sam does not answer immediately. He looks at the fire and then says: <em>"I'm useful."</em> Thomas Jay says nothing. This is not the same thing.
  <div class="lore-note teal">📌 SAM ARC: He is becoming selfish — not consciously, not cruelly. But "I am useful" instead of "I am happy" is the answer of someone who has replaced joy with purpose, and purpose is becoming an excuse to ignore the people around him.</div></td></tr>

  <tr class="sam-arc"><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 58</span><span class="official-title">"Highway to Heaven"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-low">Low</span></td><td></td><td>Dimension Light</td><td><span class="badge-notstarted">NOT STARTED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-sam">SAM</span><span class="arc-tag tag-madoria">MADORIA</span>
  Sam interrogates Madoria about her feelings for him. Not cruelly — but he needs to know, and he asks without considering what asking costs her. Madoria thinks about every time she has been treated as a data system rather than a living being. She fears attracting the Pain Master — high emotional pain produces a signal she doesn't know she has. She explores alone to process. Sam waits. He worries he pushed too hard. He did.
  <div class="lore-note teal">📌 LIGHTBRINGER: Madoria's fear of the Pain Master is instinctive — she doesn't know why high pain attracts something terrible toward her. It's because she is the Daughter of God. The Pain Master hunts sacred things as much as it hunts broken ones. The Lightbringer legacy paints a target on her back she cannot see.</div></td></tr>

  <tr class="lightbringer"><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 59</span><span class="official-title">"Distant Echoes"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-low">Low</span></td><td></td><td>Dimension Light</td><td><span class="badge-notstarted">NOT STARTED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-madoria">MADORIA</span><span class="arc-tag tag-death">DEATH</span><span class="arc-tag tag-lightbringer">LIGHTBRINGER</span>
  Madoria senses parts of herself at the border of creation — afraid to seek them. She diverts the fear into usefulness: sharing Dimensionlock bomb findings with the team. She reaches out to Death for answers about her fragments. Death meets her again. This time he brings a flower — the Flower of Death, the one Cryious found. He gives it to her. He says nothing about why. She thanks him. She puts it in her hair.
  Death leaves the meeting and sits in a corridor outside his quarters for exactly as long as it takes for the ship to complete one slow rotation around a dead star. Then he goes back inside.
  <div class="lore-note gold">📌 LIGHTBRINGER: Death giving Metrodoria's daughter the Flower of Death — a flower connected to the Gardener of Creation — is his most intimate act of the entire arc. He doesn't know he's doing it consciously. His subconscious has been connecting the dots on Madoria's identity for chapters. His emotional architecture has no label for what he just did. He is learning to build one.</div></td></tr>

  <tr class="sam-arc"><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 60</span><span class="official-title">"Joker and Viv"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-low">Low</span></td><td></td><td>Dimension Light</td><td><span class="badge-notstarted">NOT STARTED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-vivian">VIVIAN</span><span class="arc-tag tag-madoria">MADORIA</span>
  Madoria tries to reach the Alpha Superium through official channels — blocked. The King's control by the Tenebris via the Sentry is now airtight. Vivian and an unpredictable character — called "the Joker" — have a tense encounter in a neutral space. The Joker is someone who has clearly used Vivian's shapeshifted form before, or knows what he can do, and challenges him to prove who he really is. Vivian uses the Soul Splitter — the flash of the future shows him the Joker will stand down in 4 seconds. He waits. 4 seconds. The Joker stands down.
  <div class="lore-note purple">📌 VIVIAN: The Joker may be someone from his past — perhaps from a reality neighboring his own that the Leviathan Tengual also touched. The confrontation is not resolved fully here. But Vivian walks away having chosen patience over combat for the first time. His arc of calming down is real now.</div></td></tr>

  <tr class="sam-arc"><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 61</span><span class="official-title">"Koil and Sic Boi"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-low">Low</span></td><td></td><td>Dimension Light</td><td><span class="badge-notstarted">NOT STARTED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-sam">SAM</span><span class="arc-tag tag-madoria">MADORIA</span>
  Sam kidnaps an operator for intelligence on the Sentry's movements. This is reckless — he does it without consulting the team. A soul fragment of Madoria merges with her during the same operation, triggering an involuntary manifestation of her purifying ability: a brief, blinding warmth that disrupts the room. Sam did not plan for this. It creates a rift — his friends don't know how to respond to the new Madoria, and Sam doesn't understand what she just became.
  <div class="lore-note teal">📌 LIGHTBRINGER: Madoria's purifying ability surfaced involuntarily for the first time. She didn't do it consciously — a fragment of herself merged with her and the power expressed itself before she could control it. This is the beginning of her awakening as the Daughter of God.</div></td></tr>

  <tr><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 62</span><span class="official-title">"Losing Focus"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-low">Low</span></td><td></td><td>Dimension Light</td><td><span class="badge-wip">WIP</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-sam">SAM</span><span class="arc-tag tag-madoria">MADORIA</span>
  Sam's friends debate whether to accept the merged Madoria. Sam seeks outside help. The team fractures — each person's arc pulling in different direction. The mission is losing its center. Madoria is quiet during the debate. She does not defend herself. She is beginning to reach her limit — not of capability, but of giving without receiving. The shine she always had is dimming.
  <div class="lore-note teal">📌 MADORIA ARC: <em>"We see her break down and reach the limit of what she can sacrifice."</em> This is the beginning of that limit. Her arc parallels Elystria's in one key way: both give everything for others. Both will have to learn that giving without reservation destroys the giver.</div></td></tr>

  <tr class="ely-arc"><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 63</span><span class="official-title">"Trouble in the Sphere"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-low">Low</span></td><td></td><td>Death Faction</td><td><span class="badge-wip">WIP</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-ely">ELYSTRIA</span><span class="arc-tag tag-vivian">VIVIAN</span><span class="arc-tag tag-flybutt">FLYBUTT</span>
  Elystria requests Vivian for a diplomatic mission. Flybutt goes with May on land scouting to build relay towers. Flybutt, without being asked, helps far more people during the scouting mission than the assignment required — going out of his way for every soul he encounters. He returns quieter than usual. Something about what real care looks like, repeatedly, one person at a time, has recalibrated him. He lands on May's hat that night. She lets him stay there.
  <div class="lore-note green">📌 FLYBUTT ARC: <em>"Flybutt regrets not being her real father."</em> He is not her real father. He was a failed attempt at recreating someone. But in this scouting mission he finds out what a father does: shows up repeatedly, for everyone, without being asked. He returns knowing who he has been being all along. And he does not know how to tell May.</div></td></tr>

  <tr class="ely-arc"><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 64</span><span class="official-title">"Tendrils of Madness PT1"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-low">Low</span></td><td></td><td>Death Faction</td><td><span class="badge-wip">WIP</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-ely">ELYSTRIA</span><span class="arc-tag tag-vivian">VIVIAN</span><span class="arc-tag tag-iza">IZA</span>
  Vivian and Elystria's diplomatic mission: protecting a newly formed reaper in a newly formed reality. The reaper is terrified, newly appointed by Death's Card. Elystria guides them with her elemental magic — gentle, not imposing. Vivian watches. At one point Elystria puts her hand on the new reaper's shoulder and says: <em>"You don't have to feel nothing. You just have to keep going."</em> She doesn't look at Vivian when she says it. But she is saying it to him too.
  Later: Vivian asks her directly — <em>"Do you still blame May?"</em> Elystria is quiet for a long time. Then: <em>"I think I'm running out of blame."</em>
  <div class="lore-note" style="background:#fde0dc; border-left-color:#880e4f;">📌 ELYSTRIA ARC: "Running out of blame" is not the same as forgiveness. But it is the thing that comes right before it. This is the conversation that changed her. She didn't arrive here by being told to forgive. She arrived by exhausting the energy that kept the blame alive.</div></td></tr>

  <tr class="ely-arc"><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 65</span><span class="official-title">"Tendrils of Madness PT2"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-low">Low</span></td><td></td><td>Death Faction</td><td><span class="badge-wip">WIP</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-ely">ELYSTRIA</span><span class="arc-tag tag-agitator">AGITATOR</span><span class="arc-tag tag-may">MAY</span>
  A BURDEN TO THOSE WHO SEE — An uneasy alliance: the Agitator of Sin, Death's crew, for a surprise attack on the Lurker to detonate the Obsidian Bomb. The Sentry appears in the same space, pursuing the Tenebris's separate mission — it is not there for the Lurker, not there for the crew. Three-way chaos. The Agitator's body-control ability is used in the field — his Sniper's hand is briefly controlled to take a shot the Sniper would not have taken. The Sniper is aware it happened. He files it away. Elystria makes a choice in this battle that betrays one of her own beliefs — sacrificing the ideals of a diplomat to protect May in a moment of pure defensive instinct. She does not regret it. She is surprised she doesn't.
  <div class="lore-note" style="background:#fde0dc; border-left-color:#880e4f;">📌 ELYSTRIA ARC: <em>"She starts to make decisions that aren't so kind anymore to protect May."</em> This is that shift. She is no longer just kind. She is fierce. And in being fierce for May, she has found something she thought she lost: a reason to be something more than sad.</div></td></tr>

  <tr class="pivot"><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 66</span><span class="official-title">"Tendrils of Madness PT3"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-low">Low</span></td><td></td><td>Death Faction</td><td><span class="badge-wip">WIP</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-ely">ELYSTRIA</span><span class="arc-tag tag-lurker">LURKER</span>
  <span class="milestone">⚡ PIVOT — ELYSTRIA INFECTED WITH THE MADNESS</span>
  The Lurker — on its own agenda, using its Fragmented Madness and apple-distribution ability — traps Elystria and infects her. It uses its Soul Snire-adjacent capability to breach her emotional expressiveness and plant the Madness directly into her. The Lurker chose her because she is the most emotionally expressive reaper — more emotional surface area means faster infection spread. It is not personal. It is tactical. The Lurker is still 5 steps ahead.
  Sam and Madoria retreat with their friends. The Sentry observes the battle outcome from a distance — indifferent to the Lurker's actions, focused entirely on its Tenebris-given mission. Death begins planning the most drastic next actions.
  <div class="lore-note">📌 LURKER: He infected Elystria because of her emotional surface area — high expressiveness means the Madness spreads faster. He envies May because she carries the Madness inside her. Infecting Elystria is also a strike at May: destroy the person who is May's best friend, the person who is teaching May how to feel. The Lurker knows exactly what he's doing. He is always 5 steps ahead.</div></td></tr>

