<div class="section-title">▶ ACT 5 — THE LONG DARK (Ch. 67–76)</div>

<table><thead><tr>
  <th style="width:15%;">CHAPTER</th><th style="width:8%;">PRIORITY</th><th style="width:7%;">SOURCE</th>
  <th style="width:10%;">FACTION</th><th style="width:8%;">STATUS</th><th>OVERVIEW &amp; ARC NOTES</th>
</tr></thead><tbody>

  <tr class="suggested"><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 67</span><span class="official-title">"Battle ARC"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-low">Low</span></td><td></td><td>Death Faction</td><td><span class="badge-wip">WIP</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-may">MAY</span><span class="arc-tag tag-vivian">VIVIAN</span><span class="arc-tag tag-cryious">CRYIOUS</span><span class="arc-tag tag-flybutt">FLYBUTT</span>
  THE WEIGHT OF WHAT WE CARRIED — Aftermath. The crew is silent. May goes cold and mission-only. Vivian tries to reach her and fails. Death gives his rare speech: not comfort, just clarity — what comes next, what it will cost, no grief yet. Cryious stands by Flybutt. Flybutt asks: <em>"Do you think she'll be okay?"</em> Cryious doesn't answer. Then, quietly: <em>"She's a reaper."</em> Flybutt thinks about the child on the bridge, and May's single tear, and all the things a reaper technically shouldn't be able to do that May keeps doing anyway. <em>"Yeah,"</em> he says. <em>"She is."</em>
  <div class="lore-note green">📌 FLYBUTT ARC: This is the bravest thing he has said all arc. He believes in May — not despite her emotions, but because of them. This is where his arc of growing braver arrives. He is no longer cautious. He is certain.</div></td></tr>

  <tr class="suggested"><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 68</span><span class="official-title">"Battle of Devotis Realiotus"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-low">Low</span></td><td></td><td>Death Faction</td><td><span class="badge-notstarted">NOT STARTED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-death">DEATH</span><span class="arc-tag tag-cryious">CRYIOUS</span>
  THE SENTRY MOVES — The Sentry (acting on the Tenebris's orders) strikes three realities simultaneously — corrupting reaper networks, leaving them defenseless. Not the Lurker's destruction style at all: precise, strategic, targeted. Death is visibly shaken. He has Death Fraction power capable of decimating armies in seconds — but he cannot sense the Lurker or things from the Real World. The Sentry is moving at a strategic level that suggests a mind above it. Intelligence reaches Death: the Sentry has been near Sidney's last known location. He says nothing to May.
  <div class="lore-note gold">📌 DEATH: He cannot sense the Lurker due to its Real World origin. He is also beginning to suspect he cannot fully sense the Tenebris either. He is, for the first time in his existence, operating with incomplete information. A being of total administrative certainty having to improvise is more frightening to him than any enemy.</div></td></tr>

  <tr class="death-arc"><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 69</span><span class="official-title">"Scorn of Terror"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-low">Low</span></td><td></td><td>Death Faction</td><td><span class="badge-notstarted">NOT STARTED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-death">DEATH</span>
  Death finds Dante — old operator, survivor of Zero Point. Dante was there before Leviathan Protocol 14 activated. He testifies about the Sentry's first known appearance — which predates the Lurker entirely. The Sentry was the Tenebris's arm before the Lurker even arrived. Dante describes what he saw: something that felt like it came from below Creation, from a level that shouldn't have life in it. Death listens. He does not write anything down. He doesn't need to.
  <div class="lore-note gold">📌 DEATH ARC: This is his peak information chapter. He now has the full picture — the Tenebris, the Sentry, the Lurker, and how none of them are the same thing. He has always been certain. He is now more certain than ever — and the certainty contains knowledge he doesn't want to have.</div></td></tr>

  <tr class="char-arc"><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 70</span><span class="official-title">"Revelations of Fear"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-critical">Critical</span></td><td></td><td>Death Faction</td><td><span class="badge-notstarted">NOT STARTED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-may">MAY</span><span class="arc-tag tag-vivian">VIVIAN</span><span class="arc-tag tag-ely">ELYSTRIA</span>
  May attempts to kill Vivian for not letting her save Elystria. She is using her Reaper Blade — daggers, Kronen (bladed tonfas) — aggressive, acrobatic, inelegant, full-speed. She is not thinking. Vivian does not draw the Soul Splitter. He does not shift. He blocks everything by hand. He absorbs the hits. He holds her when she runs out of energy. He says: <em>"You are allowed to love her. That is not weakness. That is why you are the only reaper I have ever trusted."</em> May breaks.
  Elystria, elsewhere, visits old memories — her husband, her daughter, the day the building fell. She is not sad in the memory. She is present. She says goodbye to the version of herself that blamed everyone.
  <div class="lore-note purple">📌 VIVIAN ARC COMPLETE: He came onto this ship impulsive, arrogant, a lone wolf with no one left. He ends this chapter as someone who can hold another person's grief without flinching, without needing to fix it, without running. That is his arc. That is 70 chapters of growth made real in one moment.</div></td></tr>

  <tr class="ely-arc"><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 71</span><span class="official-title">"The Win"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-low">Low</span></td><td></td><td>Death Faction</td><td><span class="badge-notstarted">NOT STARTED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-ely">ELYSTRIA</span>
  PAINFUL TIMES AHEAD — Despite the Madness, Elystria secures a small mission victory — protecting someone who couldn't protect themselves. Her elemental magic is fading slightly (the Madness interferes with precision). She compensates with her scythe-whip, which she uses more readily now than she ever did before. It surprises her team. She surprises herself. She chose her scythe. She chose to stay in the fight. She chose to be a reaper.
  <div class="lore-note" style="background:#fde0dc; border-left-color:#880e4f;">📌 ELYSTRIA: <em>"She doesn't want to be a reaper and live forever."</em> But choosing her scythe here is not about wanting reaper life. It is about choosing to be useful with the life she has left. There is a difference. She knows the difference now.</div></td></tr>

  <tr class="ely-arc"><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 72</span><span class="official-title">"Good Gods"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-low">Low</span></td><td></td><td>Death Faction</td><td><span class="badge-notstarted">NOT STARTED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-ely">ELYSTRIA</span><span class="arc-tag tag-iza">IZA</span>
  Elystria prepares her contingency — a way to preserve what she knows before she dies. She knows who the new Gardener of Creation is. She will die before she can tell anyone directly. So she does something else: she tells Iza. Not in words. She gives him the note he kept from Ch. 49 — about the warmth that felt like it came from inside Creation — and adds one line to it in her own handwriting. She folds it. She tells him to keep it.
  <div class="lore-note green">📌 GARDENER OF CREATION THREAD: The identity of the new Gardener is passed forward through Elystria's note to Iza. He doesn't know what he's holding. He keeps it because Elystria asked him to. This is the most important thing he does all arc — and it looks like nothing.</div></td></tr>

  <tr class="death-arc"><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 73</span><span class="official-title">"Bad Gods"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-low">Low</span></td><td></td><td>Death Faction</td><td><span class="badge-notstarted">NOT STARTED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-death">DEATH</span>
  Death visits the old garden of creation — the Dimension Lock fractures have reached here too. He meets a ghost of his early days: a vision or echo of the first reaper he ever appointed, standing in the original garden. The ghost says nothing. It simply points to where the garden is still growing. Death looks. In the corner of the dying garden, untouched by the fractures: the Rasker Flower. Gabriel Forge's father's unfinished legacy. Growing. Death knows what this means. He stays there for a very long time.
  <div class="lore-note purple">📌 VIVIAN CONNECTION: The Rasker Flower his father never taught him to grow — it's been in the garden all along. The Gardener of Creation knows this. Death knows this. He will not tell Vivian. Not yet. Some things must be found, not given.</div></td></tr>

  <tr class="suggested"><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 74</span><span class="official-title">"Gods of the Beyonder"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-low">Low</span></td><td></td><td>Death Faction</td><td><span class="badge-suggested">SUGGESTED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-death">DEATH</span><span class="arc-tag tag-may">MAY</span><span class="arc-tag tag-vivian">VIVIAN</span>
  ALL ROADS BREAK EVENTUALLY — The Dimensionlock bomb is confirmed ready. Final briefing. The plan targets the Lurker's occupied reality. The Sentry is an independent danger to be navigated around. May is assigned to deliver the bomb to the core. She asks: <em>"What happens to whoever delivers it?"</em> Death does not answer. The silence says enough. Death pulls May aside privately — tells her something about her. Not about the mission. About who she has become. He speaks in his flat, emotionless voice. The words are not flat at all. May almost takes off her hat. She doesn't. Vivian hears it through the door. He reaches for her hand that night. She doesn't pull away.
  <div class="lore-note gold">📌 DEATH ARC PEAK: He told May something true about her. That is the most emotionally advanced thing he has done in his entire existence. He didn't do it well. His voice didn't change. His face didn't move. But he said it — and she heard it — and that is everything.</div></td></tr>

  <tr class="ely-arc"><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 75</span><span class="official-title">"Count My Deeds"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-low">Low</span></td><td></td><td>Death Faction</td><td><span class="badge-notstarted">NOT STARTED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-ely">ELYSTRIA</span>
  <span class="milestone">⭐ ELYSTRIA ARC COMPLETE</span>
  ELYSTRIA BACKSTORY — A full chapter. She counts what she has done since becoming a reaper. She thinks of her husband and daughter — not with the knife-edge of grief but with something softer. She has moved on (Theme 1). She has forgiven May and herself (Theme 2). She has found goodness in a world infinitely evil (Theme 3). She has cherished what is close to her (Theme 4 — Vivian, Kiza's memory, the crew). She does not regret her life. She does not want to die. But she is not afraid of it. She is ready to choose it if she must.
  <div class="lore-note" style="background:#fde0dc; border-left-color:#880e4f;">📌 All four themes are resolved for Elystria. Her arc is complete. Her death is near. This is the story honoring her before the ending takes her. She was a sunflower. She found another sun.</div></td></tr>

  <tr class="char-arc"><td><span class="chapter-link">CH 76</span><span class="official-title">"Ghostly Interference"</span></td>
  <td><span class="badge-low">Low</span></td><td></td><td>Death Faction</td><td><span class="badge-notstarted">NOT STARTED</span></td>
  <td><span class="arc-tag tag-flybutt">FLYBUTT</span><span class="arc-tag tag-cryious">CRYIOUS</span><span class="arc-tag tag-vivian">VIVIAN</span><span class="arc-tag tag-ely">ELYSTRIA</span>
  BEFORE THE STARS GO OUT — The night before the final mission. Flybutt watches May sleep and carves something small using a soul seed connoisseur's precision — he leaves it by her side. Cryious stands at the ship's edge reciting his longest list of names yet. He doesn't know Elystria is in the corridor behind him. She places lavender — his favorite — outside his door and walks on without looking back. Vivian tries to write a letter. Can't find the words. Folds the blank page into his pocket. Elystria and Vivian sit together one final time. She tells him something. We don't hear it. He holds her hands. She smiles. May is already awake. She has been awake all night. She stares at her hat.
  <div class="lore-note gold">📌 THEME 4: Cherish the things close to us. This entire chapter is that theme — embodied in silence, in small gestures, in the last time each of these people chooses to be present with each other before everything changes. No dialogue is needed. The actions speak.</div></td></tr>

