  CRYIOUS — His final chapter. The Lurker gains too fast. Cryious turns and faces it. He activates Static Freeze — the bubble that drains his stamina — and holds the Lurker inside it for as long as he can. Flashback: the names he recites. Who they were. The 2nd Reality. The first souls he ever reaped. He has carried them all this time. He lets the Freeze collapse on purpose when May and Vivian are far enough ahead. The Sentry passes through the same space on its own Tenebris-directed mission — not there for Cryious, not there for the Lurker, but its passage disrupts the Freeze's collapse pattern, accelerating the outcome. Two uncoordinated forces. One consequence. Cryious is turned to ash. He is smiling. In his last second he thinks about the Rasker Flower in the garden. He thinks about Vivian. He thinks: <em>he'll find it himself.</em> May cries real tears. Vivian pulls her forward. <em>"He bought this. Don't waste it."</em>
