<div class="arc-end">
  <h3>ARC 1 END GOAL — COMPLETE SUMMARY</h3>
  <p><strong>THE LURKER</strong> — stopped. By May and the Obsidian bomb. The Lurker was a former scientist who became a demented, obsessive force of corruption from outside Creation. He envied May's Madness and competed with the Tenebris for the Pure Madness. He is gone. He was 5 steps ahead his whole arc — until May was 6.</p>
  <p><strong>THE TENEBRIS</strong> — revealed (Ch. 77, through the Sentry) as the true enemy. Ancient, patient, the thing that killed Metrodoria Lightbringer in the prologue, the puppet master controlling the King through the Sentry. The war has just been named. Arc 2 brings it fully into the open.</p>
  <p><strong>DEATHS:</strong> Kiza (Ch. 14), Cryious (Ch. 83), Flybutt (Ch. 84), Elystria (referenced in the finale — her infection takes her between Ch. 85 and Arc 2). May and Vivian are reborn. Death's ship is destroyed.</p>
  <p><strong>THE LIGHTBRINGER THREAD:</strong> Metrodoria Lightbringer was killed by the Tenebris. Her daughter Madoria AI has been recovering fragments of herself all arc — including her ability to purify the Madness. Death gave her the Flower of Death. He has known who she is. He has never said. He hunts Sidney now — the key to the Tenebris — with Madoria's awakening as the counter-force. Arc 2 is her story too.</p>
  <p><strong>FOUR THEMES RESOLVED:</strong><br>
  1. <em>Learning to move on</em> — Sam: chose not to bring Sidney back. May: reborn forward.<br>
  2. <em>Learning to forgive oneself</em> — Elystria: ran out of blame and chose forgiveness. May: began in Ch. 38 and completes in rebirth.<br>
  3. <em>Finding what it means to be good in a world infinitely evil</em> — May: reaping with care. Elystria: goodness under the Madness.<br>
  4. <em>Cherish the things close to us</em> — Flybutt: turned to stone from love. Cryious: chose to stand for his people. Elystria: chose to stay. Vivian: reborn beside May.
  </p>
  <p><strong>END OF ARC 1</strong></p>
